documentation.text:
The `XBR Network <https://github.com/crossbario/xbr-protocol/blob/master/contracts/XBRNetwork.sol>`__
 contract is the on-chain anchor of and the entry point to the XBR protocol.
Event emitted when a new member registered in the XBR Network.
Event emitted when an existing member is changed (without leaving the XBR Network).
Event emitted when a member leaves the XBR Network.
Event emitted when the payable status of a coin is changed.
Special addresses used as "any address" marker in mappings (eg coins).
Limit to how old a pre-signed transaction is accetable (eg in "registerMemberFor" and similar).
Chain ID of the blockchain this contract is running on, used in EIP712 typed data signature verification.
Verifying contract address, used in EIP712 typed data signature verification.
IPFS multihash of the `XBR Network EULA <https://github.com/crossbario/xbr-protocol/blob/master/EULA>`__.
XBR network contributions from markets for the XBR project, expressed as a fraction of the total amount of XBR tokens.
Address of the XBR Networks' own ERC20 token for network-wide purposes.
Address of the `XBR Network Organization <https://xbr.network/>`__.
Current XBR Network members ("member directory").
ERC20 coins which can specified as a means of payment when creating a new data market.

params.account: The account to grant maintainer rights to.

params.networkToken: The token to run this network itself on. Note that XBR data markets can use                     any ERC20 token (enabled in the ``coins`` mapping of this contract) as                     a means of payment in the respective market.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getRoleMember(bytes32,uint256).details: Returns one of the accounts that have `role`. `index` must be a value between 0 and {getRoleMemberCount}, non-inclusive. Role bearers are not sorted in any particular way, and their ordering may change at any point. WARNING: When using {getRoleMember} and {getRoleMemberCount}, make sure you perform all queries on the same block. See the following https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/iterating-over-elements-on-enumerableset-in-openzeppelin-contracts/2296[forum post] for more information.

getRoleMemberCount(bytes32).details: Returns the number of accounts that have `role`. Can be used together with {getRoleMember} to enumerate all bearers of a role.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

returns._0: `true` if the account is maintainer, otherwise `false`.

params.memberProfile: Optional public member profile: the IPFS Multihash of the member profile stored in IPFS.
params.networkEula: Multihash of the XBR EULA being agreed to and stored as one ZIP file archive on IPFS.

params.registered: Block number at which the registering member has created the signature.
params.signature: EIP712 signature, signed by the registering member.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

params.coin: The address of the ERC20 coin to change.
params.isPayable: When true, the coin can be specified when opening a new data market.

params.networkContribution: Network contribution, defined as the ratio of given number of                            tokens and the total token supply.

returns._0: Flag indicating whether the contribution value was actually changed.

params.level: The member level to set the member to.
params.member: The address of the XBR network member to override member level.

params.networkToken: The token to run this network itself on. Note that XBR data markets can use                     any ERC20 token (enabled in the ``coins`` mapping of this contract) as                     a means of payment in the respective market.

params.retired: Block number at which the unregistering member has created the signature.
params.signature: EIP712 signature, signed by the unregistering member.

CoinChanged(address,address,bool).notice: Event emitted when the payable status of a coin is changed.

MaintainerAdded(address).notice: Event fired when a maintainer was added.

MaintainerRemoved(address).notice: Event fired when a maintainer was removed.

MemberChanged(address,uint256,string,str.notice: Event emitted when an existing member is changed (without leaving the XBR Network).

MemberRegistered(address,uint256,string,.notice: Event emitted when a new member registered in the XBR Network.

MemberRetired(address,uint256).notice: Event emitted when a member leaves the XBR Network.

ANYADR().notice: Special addresses used as "any address" marker in mappings (eg coins).

PRESIGNED_TXN_MAX_AGE().notice: Limit to how old a pre-signed transaction is accetable (eg in "registerMemberFor" and similar).

addMaintainer(address).notice: Add a new maintainer to the list of maintainers.

coins(address,address).notice: ERC20 coins which can specified as a means of payment when creating a new data market.

contribution().notice: XBR network contributions from markets for the XBR project, expressed as a fraction of the total amount of XBR tokens.

eula().notice: IPFS multihash of the `XBR Network EULA <https://github.com/crossbario/xbr-protocol/blob/master/EULA>`__.

isMaintainer(address).notice: Check if the given address is currently a maintainer.

registerMember(string,string).notice: Register the sender of this transaction in the XBR network. All XBR stakeholders, namely data providers ("sellers"), data consumers ("buyers") and data market operators, must be registered in the XBR network.

registerMemberFor(address,uint256,string.notice: Register the specified new member in the XBR Network. All XBR stakeholders, namely data providers ("sellers"), data consumers ("buyers") and data market operators, must be registered in the XBR network. Note: This version uses pre-signed data where the actual blockchain transaction is submitted by a gateway paying the respective gas (in ETH) for the blockchain transaction.

setCoinPayable(address,address,bool).notice: Set ERC20 coins as usable as a means of payment when opening data markets.

setContribution(uint256).notice: Set the network contribution which is deducted from the market fees defined by a market operator.

setMemberLevel(address,uint8).notice: Set (override manually) the member level of a XBR Network member. Being able to do so currently serves two purposes: - having a last resort to handle situation where members violated the EULA - being able to manually patch things in error/bug cases

setNetworkOrganization(address).notice: Set the XBR network organization address.

setNetworkToken(address).notice: Set the XBR network organization address.

token().notice: Address of the XBR Networks' own ERC20 token for network-wide purposes.

unregisterMember().notice: Unregister the sender of this transaction from the XBR network.

unregisterMemberFor(address,uint256,byte.notice: Unregister the specified member from the XBR Network. Note: This version uses pre-signed data where the actual blockchain transaction is submitted by a gateway paying the respective gas (in ETH) for the blockchain transaction.

verifyingChain().notice: Chain ID of the blockchain this contract is running on, used in EIP712 typed data signature verification.

verifyingContract().notice: Verifying contract address, used in EIP712 typed data signature verification.

userdoc.notice: The `XBR Network <https://github.com/crossbario/xbr-protocol/blob/master/contracts/XBRNetwork.sol>`__ contract is the on-chain anchor of and the entry point to the XBR protocol.
